-- Dogan Yayin Declines in Istanbul After 2011 Loss Widens
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-04-09T15:23:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/dogan-yayin-declines-in-istanbul-after-2011-loss-widens.html
Dogan Yayin Holding AS (DYHOL) , a Turkish
media holding company, fell in Istanbul after reporting a loss
of 1.2 billion liras ($667 million) last year, exceeding
estimates.  Dogan Yayin dropped 1.2 percent to 82 kurus at the close in
Istanbul.  The company was expected to report a loss of 1.1 billion
liras, according to the average of four analyst estimates
compiled by Bloomberg. It posted a loss of 237 million liras in
2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
